      "content": "# 🚀 GET `/user` - Retrieve User Profile\nThis critical endpoint fetches comprehensive profile data for the currently authenticated CloudScale user.\n\n### 🧭 Overview & Purpose\nThis document strictly details the functionality for retrieving user metadata; please note all required contextual headers below.\n\n### 📡 Request Specifications\n*   **HTTP Method:** `GET`\n*   **Endpoint Path:** `/user`\n*   **Query Parameters:** *None permitted.*\n*   **Required Headers:** `Authorization` (Format: Bearer Token), `Accept` (`application/json`), `Cache-Control` (`max-age=3600`), and `Accept-Encoding` (`gzip`).\n\n### 📬 Response Schemas\n#### Success Response (`200 OK`)\nThe response payload conforms to the `UserProfileData` object, containing `user_id`, `username`, and `email`. Key response headers include `Content-Location` and standardized `RateLimit-Remaining`.\n\n#### Error Responses\n*   `401 Unauthorized`: Missing or invalid `Authorization` header.\n*   `500 Internal Server Error`: Backend system failure; check server logs.",
